etymology.description: 竹(竹) (zhú, 'bamboo') + 奚(奚) (xī, 'what') = phonetic component 奚 (xī) with bamboo radical -> phonetic character
etymology.interpretation: The character 𥏻 combines the bamboo radical 竹(竹) (zhú, 'bamboo') with the phonetic component 奚(奚) (xī, 'what'), suggesting that it involves something related to bamboo, guided by the phonetic cue of 'xī'.
